  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e31" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Repealed</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1-3</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>Repealed. [B.C. Reg. 214/2009, s. (b).]</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e43">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Applicant may appeal</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>4</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>If an applicant for a development permit within an intensive residential development area is refused a development permit by the planning director or delegate responsible for issuing development permits or the applicant objects to a proposed provision of the development permit, the applicant may appeal the decision to council.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Reg. 214/2009, s. (b).]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e58">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Repealed</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>5</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>Repealed. [B.C. Reg. 214/2009, s. (b).]</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e70">
      <bcl:marginalnote>City may make different regulations</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>6</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The City of Victoria may, under section 479 (1) of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/r15001_00" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Local Government Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, make regulations that are different, as specified in a bylaw, for different structures depending on the age of the structure.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Reg. 118/2018, s. 2.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/r15001_00" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Local Government Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 2015, c. 1, s. 296]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
